    <abstract><!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
      <para>
       The topoic covers joining an Active Directory domain using <command>adcli</command>
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
    On &productnameshort; you need to first join an active directory domain. To do so, use the
    <command>adcli</command> command, which creates a computer account for the machine joining the
    domain and if Kerberos is used, a keytab is created for the machine.
   </para>
   <screen>&prompt.sudo;adcli join <replaceable>OPTIONS</replaceable>
   <replaceable>DOMAIN_NAME</replaceable></screen>
   <para>
    You can specify the following options:
   </para>
   <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>-O, --domain-ou=OU=<replaceable>OU_NAME</replaceable></term>
      <listitem>
<para>
  Specify a full name of the organisational unit in which the computer account will be created.
</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>-N, --computer-name=<replaceable>COMPUTER_NAME</replaceable></term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
   <para>
    After you join a domain, the command enables you to perform further actions in that
    domain. For details, refer to <xref linkend=""/>.
   </para>
</topic>
